Nor can blows from without hold together all the sum which has been brought into union. They can it is true frequently impinge upon and stay a part, until others come and the sum can be completed. At times how- ever they are compelled to rebound and in so doing grant to the first- beginnings of things room and time for flight, to enable them to get clear away from the mass in union. Wherefore again and again I repeat many bodies must rise up 3 nay more that the blows themselves may not fail, there is need of an infinite supply of matter on all sides.
